question:
District category contains Ancient City, Manufacturing District, and Silicon Valley.
Supermarkets category contains WinCo Foods, Wegmans, and Fry's.
The number of each Ancient City 's Wegmans equals 10 more than the sum of each Silicon Valley 's Wegmans and each Ancient City 's Fry's.
The number of each Ancient City 's WinCo Foods equals 22 times the difference of each Silicon Valley 's Wegmans and each Ancient City 's Fry's.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's WinCo Foods equals 4 times each Silicon Valley 's Wegmans.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Fry's equals 3.
The number of each Ancient City 's Fry's equals 13 more than each Silicon Valley 's Wegmans.
The number of each Silicon Valley 's Wegmans equals 12.
How many Supermarkets does Ancient City have?
solution:
Define each Silicon Valley 's Wegmans as z; So z = 12.
Define each Ancient City 's Fry's as g; So g = 13 + z = 13 + 12 = 2.
Define each Ancient City 's Wegmans as p; i = z + g = 12 + 2 = 14; So p = 10 + i = 10 + 14 = 1.
Define each Ancient City 's WinCo Foods as P; R = z - g = 12 - 2 = 10; So P = 22 * R = 22 * 10 = 13.
Define each Ancient City 's Supermarkets as Q; J = g + p = 2 + 1 = 3; So Q = P + J = 13 + 3 = 16.
